<item>
            <title>[SOLR-14205] Do not fail when given timeout to connectionImpl.isValid() = 0</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-14205</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The ConnectionImpl.isValid() returns false when you pass 0 as the timeout. According to the javadocs (&lt;a href=&quot;https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/11/docs/api/java.sql/java/sql/Connection.html#isValid(int)&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/11/docs/api/java.sql/java/sql/Connection.html#isValid(int)&lt;/a&gt;)&#160;a timeout = 0 means no timeout. In the current implementation a timeout = 0 means that the connection is always invalid.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
